00:43:53.459 --> 00:43:56.963
It says I can be known and not abandoned.

00:43:57.804 --> 00:43:59.826
And that doesn't cure us, confession.

00:44:00.098 --> 00:44:06.188
But it does, like Tyler said, restores dignity and it brings us back into the light where shame begins to lose its power.

00:44:07.450 --> 00:44:08.712
Now next is witnesses.

00:44:08.812 --> 00:44:14.060
Confession is made powerful by a community of witnesses and some of us are experiencing this week after week.

00:44:14.841 --> 00:44:18.127
A witness is someone who knows your struggle without becoming your judge.

00:44:18.948 --> 00:44:22.914
So someone who can see your patterns and at the same time still see your goodness.

00:44:23.535 --> 00:44:27.922
Someone who helps you remember who you are when vanity tries to rewrite that story within you.

00:44:28.482 --> 00:44:32.628
and we don't heal vanity through willpower, we've all tried it and let's be honest, it didn't work.

00:44:33.389 --> 00:44:40.859
We heal it like we've been saying through presence, through people who can say, I see you and you are still good.

00:44:42.341 --> 00:44:48.790
Now that leaves sobriety, meaning I have to identify and reject the compulsions that feed vanity's lies in me.

00:44:49.851 --> 00:44:57.682
So what for me uniquely and individually feeds that cultural vanity story that identifies goodness by some lesser measure

00:44:57.986 --> 00:44:58.687
than my maker.

00:44:59.648 --> 00:45:00.328
Is it shopping?

00:45:00.348 --> 00:45:01.529
Is it calorie counting?

00:45:01.630 --> 00:45:03.531
Is it an attachment to exercise?

00:45:03.592 --> 00:45:09.677
Sometimes sobriety in a place of vanity will feel like an addict counting the first 90 days.

00:45:09.718 --> 00:45:14.602
It'll feel like a grind a long time usually before it feels like a way of being.

00:45:14.642 --> 00:45:18.046
It will feel like loss before it feels like gain, which I know is encouraging.

00:45:18.386 --> 00:45:21.289
It'll also feel like restraint more than it feels like freedom.

00:45:22.971 --> 00:45:24.232
But here's the question we have to hold.

00:45:24.292 --> 00:45:26.514
Who knows not only my diagnosis

00:45:27.138 --> 00:45:28.680
my personal path to freedom.

00:45:29.722 --> 00:45:30.243
That's hope.

00:45:30.423 --> 00:45:31.525
That's life in the kingdom.

